=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Two-Calc Chain Variant) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  MOVE01 -> calc stage 0
C  REVR00 -> calc stage 1 over the current calc result
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: the tiny parsed C-spec subset can now carry a second calc slot,
  and slot 1 can transform the current calc result via source selector 00.
- This variant chains MOVE01 into REVR00, so the second calc stage reverses
  the first stage output before formatting the detail line.

Current runtime-produced output:
A10 DROCER
B20 DROCER
C30 DROCER

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_chain.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
